properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 3 at 2:15PM PST until February 5 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Combined seas 8 to 12 feet, becoming 10 to 15 feet
Tuesday afternoon. Bar conditions moderate to rough, becoming
rough to severe.

* WHERE...Grays Harbor Bar.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 10 PM PST this
evening. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 4 PM Tuesday to 7
AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft
especially when navigating in or near harbor entrances.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Maximum ebb currents will occur around
midnight tonight and 12:30PM Tuesday.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory for rough bar means that wave conditions
are expected to be hazardous to small craft in or near harbor
entrances.
